    <text xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
        <body>
            <head>211. Notes of a Meeting<note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d211fn1"
                    >Source: Reagan Library, <persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo"
                        >Carlucci</persName> Files, Secretary Shultz (08/14/1987–11/03/1987)
                    [Meetings with President—Notes]. Secret. Drafted by <persName
                        corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName>.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1987-09-17"
                        >September 17, 1987</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p rendition="simple_centre">
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">PRESIDENT</persName>’S MEETING WITH SECRETARY
                    <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">SHULTZ</persName> AND <persName
                    corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">FRANK CARLUCCI</persName> ON SEPTEMBER 17, 1987 IN
                THE OVAL OFFICE</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">GS</persName>
                <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss>—Need move. Explains 4800. <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID"
                    >Mobiles</rs>—difficult verify.</p>
            <p>
                <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Geneva</rs>—<rs
                    corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> of <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobiles</rs>—work in parallel—develop—<rs
                    corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> issues. (S&amp;G
                agree to explore <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> of
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobiles</rs> at <rs type="event"
                    corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Geneva</rs>!)</p>
            <p>S Preservation of <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs>. We have
                good options. Let’s not add complications. 10 years observe strictly.</p>
            <pb facs="0936" n="909" xml:id="pg_909"/>
            <p>As for <rs type="topic" corresp="recJclekZAp3yKmD5">R&amp;T</rs>,<note n="2"
                    place="foot" xml:id="d211fn2">Research and testing.</note> we have made steps to
                accommodate you. Third possibility is list of devices banned from space. Have given
                to your experts.</p>
            <p>There will be no retreat from preservation of <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                for 10 years. Otherwise no <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss>.</p>
            <p>Situation not hopeless. If want <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss>, a solution can be found.</p>
            <p>S Need to prod our delegations—Ministers must intervene.</p>
            <p>Must have progress on <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss> before Summit. Ground work for discussion only—Difficulties in <orgName
                    corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> re <gloss target="#t_INF_1">
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="reclckIw9AgH05Yxw">INF</rs>
                </gloss> ratif if no progress toward <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss>. Can’t have <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">GS</persName> sign
                agreement US <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> might not
                ratify.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">GS</persName> Sign agreement—fine.</p>
            <p>All other areas of R/C, bilateral, regional—broad ranging discussion.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
